Defendant Cynthia Corren Wright in court with attorney Geoffrey R Misfeldt.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  ENTRY MADE WITHOUT COURT FILE.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to 14CM004687.  Huber privileges apply for child care, elder care, school and any treatment.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 2 years.
Conditions:  
*  Any conditions set forth by the probation department;
*  Participate in any counseling deemed appropriate for mental health issues;
*  No contact with DSW, Sendiks or Menard's;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
